# Allowlist: ignore everything by default, then un-ignore the specific
# inputs the Docker build needs. This keeps the Dockerfile's `COPY . .`
# simple while making "what goes into the image" reviewable in one place.
#
# Add to this list whenever a new build-time input is introduced.

*

# Manifests + lockfile (install layer).
!package.json
!pnpm-lock.yaml

# Build config.
!svelte.config.js
!vite.config.ts
!tsconfig.json

# Source the build reads.
!src
!static

# Repo scripts (the root `prepare` lifecycle invokes one of these during
# `pnpm install`; it no-ops outside a git checkout but must exist on disk).
!scripts
